Definition: a word or phrase apparently modifying an unintended word because of its placement in a sentence: e.g., `when young' in `when young, circuses appeal to all of us'
Synonyms: misplaced_modifier, modifier, a, word, or, phrase, apparently, modifying, an, unintended, because, of, its, placement, in, sentence, e, g, when, young, circuses, appeal, to, all, us
Category: noun.communication
